topic.title: [solved] Still confused about 15441, does my ISP blocked it?
topic.body:
The result from port checker is "Port 15441 is closed".
I don't have any router (or do I? I use an android phone for tethering to my laptop).

If the result from port checker is like above, does it mean I can't open it?

1_1PjeSCAGvzNm4UxEqydwzCgQwCXEKc8ikf.body:
> [petercxy](#comment_8_1DXR2Di8Ks9JijfNycWErpenoxxchrdWBB): Do you connect to the Internet via your phone's cellular network? If so, it is highly possible that you have no public IP address.

Yes, it's cell network and I have no public IP.
Okay, I think it's clear know. Thank you.

> [thisguy1337](#comment_39_16bxMyoL49mWYhcZKBYVBT5zEFW9SQpiao): Looks like it's due to the tethering of your mobile device.  They make for poor routers  
> Have you tried something like:https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=at.bherbst.net&hl=en  
> Android Debug Bridgehttp://developer.android.com/tools/help/adb.html#forwardports

Tried that PF but failed. 
I should understand that a cell network have no public IP.  Seems like I have zero knowledge about networking.
Thanks for yor help.
